  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a clay pot over medium heat. ",
    "Add onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. ",
    "Add ginger, garlic, cumin, coriander, and red chili peppers; cook for another 2 minutes. ",
    "Add tomato paste and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. ",
    "Add fermented black beans, water, and tempering chocolate. ",
    "Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes. ",
    "Season with salt and pepper to taste. ",
    "Garnish with fresh parsley and serve over couscous. ",
    "Let the tagine rest for 10 minutes before serving. ",
    "Serve hot and enjoy! ",
    "Share with friends and family, if you have enough to spare. "
  ],
